title: The Works of Edgar Allan Poe, Raven Edition, Volume 3
creator: Edgar Allan Poe
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Works of Edgar Allan Poe, Raven Edition, Volume 3, by Edgar Allan Poe. Read by volunteer readers. This, the third of 5 volumes containing Poe's works, contains 6 of his short stories as well as Poe's only complete novel, The Narrative of A. Gordon Pym. In it, Arthur Gordon Pym stows away on a whaling vessel and experiences shipwreck, mutiny, and other adventures in typical Poe fashion. (Introduction by TriciaG) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
